Version pscom-4.1.3:
====================

2004-09-28  Norbert Eicker  <eicker@par-tec.com>

	* ChangeLog: Update ChangeLog. Prepare for release 4.1.4.

	* Bugfix: Setup the xhdr correctly in PSP_IProbeFrom() and
	  PSP_ProbeFrom(). Otherwise MPI_Probe() and MPI_Iprobe will not
	  work as defined in the standard.

2004-09-22  Norbert Eicker  <eicker@par-tec.com>

	* Modification: New defaults for module parameters:
	- Limit MaxAcksPending to 20 per default. This increases the
	  performance whenever significant packet loss occurs.
	- Allways enable polling per default.

Version pscom-4.1.3:
====================

2004-07-22  Norbert Eicker  <eicker@par-tec.com>

	* Bugfix: Allow GM_HOME and MTHOME to be set simultanously.
	Executables will try to use both, Infiniband and Myrinet (in this
	order).

2004-07-21  Jens Hauke  <hauke@par-tec.com>

	* Extension: Enable NACK's. Changed "proc" counter. Add HZ to proc.

	* Modification: Changed timeout defaults.

Version pscom-4.1.2:
====================

2004-07-13  Norbert Eicker  <eicker@par-tec.com>

	* Extension: Add new psport4all library containing all possible
	kinds of interconnects.

	* Extension: Add script for InfiniBand handling.

2004-06-22  Norbert Eicker  <eicker@par-tec.com>

	* Modification: Link against libpopt statically. This is due to
	version switch in some distros.

	* Modification:	Merge psport4b branch into main trunk.

2004-06-17  Norbert Eicker  <eicker@par-tec.com>

	* Bugfix: Also close local side of p4sock connections if the other
	side is closed. (psport4b branch)

2004-05-27  Norbert Eicker  <eicker@par-tec.com>

	* Bugfix: Merge change applied long time ago when this script
	resided within psm. Due to some unknown reasons this change was
	taken along to p4 project.

2004-05-10  Jens Hauke  <hauke@par-tec.com>

	* Bugfix: SigSegv in p4sock Path. (psport4b branch)

2004-04-29  Jens Hauke  <hauke@par-tec.com>

	* Bugfix: Truncated messages.

2004-04-08  Jens Hauke  <hauke@par-tec.com>

	* Extension: Include psport4mvapi for infiniband support.

2004-03-17  Jens Hauke  <hauke@par-tec.com>

	* Modification: 32bit support for Opteron. Dont use sys_ioctl
	anymore. (vanilla kernels dont export sys_ioctl)

2004-03-30  Jens Hauke  <hauke@par-tec.com>

	* Modification:	Changed default parameters for bcm5700.

Version pscom-4.1.1:
====================

2004-03-17  Jens Hauke  <hauke@par-tec.com>

	* Extension: 32bit support for Opteron (register ioctl's).

2004-03-03  Jens Hauke  <hauke@par-tec.com>

